body_html:
I receive the same error when Building TensorFlow in Windows 10 (without GPU version) 1.9 with Visual Studio 2015 after 2,5 hours of buidling time.

File "D:/temp/tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/cmake/build/tf_python/tensorflow/python/tools/api/generator/create_python_api.py", line 27, in from tensorflow.python.tools.api.generator import doc_srcs
ModuleNotFoundError: No module named 'tensorflow.python.tools.api'
C:\Program Files (x86)\MSBuild\Microsoft.Cpp\v4.0\V140\Microsoft.CppCommon.targets(171,5): error MSB6006: "cmd.exe" exited with code 1.

Protobuf, google and absl-py packages in the python environment were updated beforehand.

The machine that was used has 16 GB RAM and 2GB RAM for the nVidia GPU.
If someone has a clue how to avoid this error message, please help.

File "D:/temp/tensorflow/tensorflow/contrib/cmake/build/tf_python/tensorflow/python/tools/api/generator/create_python_api.py", line 27, in <module> from tensorflow.python.tools.api.generator import doc_srcs

C:\Program Files (x86)\MSBuild\Microsoft.Cpp\v4.0\V140\Microsoft.CppCommon.targets(171,5): error MSB6006: "cmd.exe" exited with code 1.
